pageContext.description: max. EB 19,Tip with pointed ellipse section, becoming 'eye-shaped' lower down with concave approaches to apexes; expands at base of fragment - here accomodating a skewed rivet hole; shape may echoe inner socket section of spearhead; few narrow facets towards tip appear distinct from wood grain. Condition: Dried out and partially mineralised; socket end seems cha[...] on outer band possibly accounting for marked thinning to rest of shaft tip - differential shinkage? break looks fresh.
